6:
Goodness, it seems the whole city
has taken to the streets celebrating.
9:
Wooow, lookit the trees! \n
They're so pretty!
12:
I had no idea Palpebra welcomes
the new year in such extravagant
style. We've at least a week before
Yamato's festivities begin.
16:
Actually... I think these are for a
Palpebran holiday. Right, Lilie?
21:
Yeppers! We hold a winter festival
each year to honor ol' Saint Nick!
29:
Mm-hm. You know, Kris Kringle? The
legendary Santa Claus? The figure
said to be the grandfather of all
sheephirds?
31:
Every winter, he dons robes of red
and travels the night sky with his
herd of flying deer, visiting every
home in Palpebra!
36:
Ah, so the lights are to keep him
away? We in Yamato also ward off
evil before the new year arrives.
42:
S-Santa isn't evil! Everyone's waitin'
for the man with the bag!
47:
By "bag," you mean his big bag of
presents, right? I heard he leaves
gifts for kids who were good all year.
51:
Exactly! He's a patron saint of
generosity, not some evil spirit,
Soushiro.
53:
That said, it's mostly a holiday for
tots and tykes to enjoy the warm,
fuzzy spirit of giving—and receiving!
58:
I see... No wonder the children are so
excited, then.
61:
I must get to work at once.\n
Would the Guild happen to have
any quests available today?
65:
I know several children who were
very good this year, and would love
to spread a bit of generosity and
cheer myself.
70:
Sounds like your wallet's on the line
then—but I know just the quest to
save it!
72:
It should be right up your alley!
Lemme just dig up the details real
quick...
78:
I greatly appreciate you lending me
traditional festival attire, Milady. I
can only hope I do it justice.
81:
Oh, goodness, you're a polite one. It's
just a silly costume, dear—no need
to be so formal. You look lovely.
84:
Ahaha, thank you. While this is my
first time wearing such an outfit, it
grows on me by the second.
87:
*psst* Help, the new part-timer's so
CUTE!
88: Shh! I heard he's already married.
89:
Nooo! But like... a man with
experience, then... Heh.
92:
...Experience? This is actually my first
time working at an establishment
such as this.
95:
For crying out loud...\n
SILENCE! I had better not hear
another PEEP of gossip, ladies!
100:
Pardon the interruption, Milady.
Might I ask for more details about
my duties as a guard?
102:
A-ahem... Of course, dear. Our
bouncer is off on vacation for the
holidays. We WERE going to have
you keeping an eye on the floor, but...
104:
Now I'm thinking it might be smarter
to have you outside attracting
customers instead of my waitresses.
106:
Yes... If I took handled the
advertising, then the waitresses
could devote themselves to serving
food.
109:
N-not exactly what I meant, but
sure. If you reel in a good crowd, I'll
even slip you a little bonus. Now go
get 'em tiger!
116:
*sigh* He's got such a sweet
smile...\n
I should've stuffed him into a cute
little maid outfit when I had the
chance...
126:
Oh? What a coincidence to see you
here, Light.
129: Hardly. I came here to stop you!
132:
I know you accepted this job to
provide for the children, b-but...
You're a teacher! A role model! Not
some e-escort.
135:
You don't belong in such an
establishment!
142:
Nothing, nothing. I merely found it
amusing how behind the times you
are.
148:
This is a themed restaurant, and
nothing more. You can be a good
role model without being a boring
old prude, Light.
156:
Ahaha, my apologies.\n
I meant no offense.
159:
Ah, "boring prude" takes me back...
My late wife often called me slow
and uptight.
163:
Oh... Iori, right? You've mentioned her
before.
166: Yes, Iori. Her words linger in my heart.
168:
Even in her absence, they provide
me with guid—
174:
You surprised me, Awa.\n
What are you three doing here?
186: We're gonna earn ALL the money!
191: Four Soushiros are faster than one!
201:
Ahaha, and I would say lightening
up changed me for the better.\n
...Look at the friends it made me.
204:
I see some of my old self in you,
Light. You are yet young—learn from
the free spirits of Alk and Stella.
212:
You need not worry about me. The
Maids' Parlor IS a bit gaudy perhaps,
but it's nothing more than a
restaurant.
214:
Would you like to step inside and
see for yourself?
220: I-I'm still not going in there! Soushiro!
225:
Wh-wh-what have you done?! The
line is out the door!
227:
Can we request specific waiters? I
wanna talk some more with Awa!
228:
Where's Mugi? I promised I'd come
play, and here I am!
233:
Ah... I am afraid "I" may have gone a
little overboard with advertising.
